title: [miHQro] Lucky Luke 1/5-15/17-40/43-46/&hellip; (1949-2012|Dgtl)
description:
" LUCKY LUKE - The man who shoots faster than his own shadow! " 

     --  series tagline

Cover:     <a href=" http://gesserit.000space.com/meta/yuq/users/29/766/YFsLthCnVQ.png" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://gesserit.000space.com/meta/yuq/users/29/766/YFsLthCnVQ.png</a>

Overview:  <a href=" http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lucky_Luke" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lucky_Luke</a>

Contains:

   The first 49 volumes of the English-language Cinebook editions, recompressed into
   the modern .webp format. Filenames have been augmented to establish the original
   publication order and to include the original release year and page resolution.
   
   Size reduction:      ~45%
   Quality reduction:   5/10   (differences are minor and rare)
   Quality sample:     <a href=" http://screenshotcomparison.com/comparison/123750" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://screenshotcomparison.com/comparison/123750</a>
   
   (cf <a href=" http://gesserit.000space.com/meta/kat/community/show/100209/?post=16373397" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://gesserit.000space.com/meta/kat/community/show/100209/?post=16373397</a>  )
   
   This is my first [miHQro] re-encode of a regular comic and directly from a JPEG
   source, which is why there is less size at more quality reduction than for the
   previous uploads. (Un)fortunately, the original digitization process appears to
   have been less than pristine, and I daresay the additional differences introduced
   by the recompression are, at worst, barely noticeable in comparison. At best,
   they're a slight improvement, eliminating more old noise than introducing new. :)
